"id":"928d6fa8-be54-4e7b-9e7d-7a98669b1266",
"notes":"The app uses the LSM6DSV16X MEMS accelerometer sensors and the Machine Learning Core embedded to detect the follow activities (the algorithm is intended for smartphone applications): Stationary, Walking, Fastwalking, Jogging, Biking and Driving.
The MLC code is embedded in the LSM6DSOX sensor, the sensor uses the 3 axes accelerometer values as input and six activities recognized as output.
For MLC code generation, four features calculated from accelerometer values have been used: mean, variance, peak-to-peak and zero-crossing.
The algorithm runs at 60 Hz, with a window of 150 samples.",
